VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT preg_replace\(([^,]+,\s*)?[^/]*e[^/]*|preg_replace\(\$_(GET|POST|REQUEST|COOKIE)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:preg_replace_callback
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects usage of preg_replace() with the /e modifier or direct use of untrusted inputs, leading to regular expression injection.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Regular Expression Injection: preg_replace with /e Modifier or Untrusted Input.
